  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Cut your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> in half (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and dice finely</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1154.step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1154.step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1154.step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1154.step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1154.step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> over a medium high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped pepper</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and a splash of <strong>cold water</strong> and cook, covered, for 8-10 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1154.step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1154.step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1154.step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1154.step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1154.step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the pepper softens, cut the <strong>chicken thighs</strong> into thick strips</p><p>Add your <strong>cornflour</strong> to a bowl with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give it a good mix</p><p>Add the <strong>chicken strips</strong> to the bowl and toss to coat them evenly in the cornflour, then set aside – this is your <strong>floured chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1154.step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1154.step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1154.step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1154.step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1154.step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> basmati rice</strong> and 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[320ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1154.step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1154.step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1154.step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1154.step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1154.step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a separate, large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with 4 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[6 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[8 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat, then add the <strong>floured chicken</strong> and cook for 4 min on each side, or until it's nice and browned (try not to turn the chicken until it's golden!)</p><p>Once golden, transfer the chicken to a baking tray (reserve the pan) and put the tray in the oven for 8-10 min or until cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>crispy chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1154.step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1154.step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1154.step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1154.step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1154.step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your<strong> red</strong> <strong>chilli relish</strong>, <strong>tomato ketchup</strong>, <strong>rice vinegar</strong>, <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>sesame oil</strong> and <strong>soy sauce</strong> with 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[60ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[70ml]</span> <strong>water</strong> and stir it all together</p><p>Add the mixture to the <strong>softened pepper</strong> and bring to the boil</p><p>Once boiling, remove the sauce from the heat – this is your <strong>Korean-style sauce</strong></p><p>Tip: If you have a food processor, blitz the sauce until smooth for a more authentic look and feel!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1154.step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1154.step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1154.step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1154.step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1154.step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>pak choi </strong>and pat it dry with kitchen paper, then cut the base off the <strong>pak choi</strong> and discard, then chop the rest finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Wipe the reserved pan clean and return it to a high heat, then once hot, add the <strong>chopped pak choi</strong> and <strong>garlic</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cook, covered, for 4 min or until it's wilted – this is your <strong>garlic pak choi</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1154.step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1154.step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1154.step-7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1154.step-7-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1154.step-7-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>garlic pak choi</strong> with the<strong> basmati rice</strong>, <strong>crispy chicken</strong> and <strong>Korean-style sauce</strong></p><p>Garnish with your <strong>black</strong> <strong>sesame seeds</strong> and <strong>toasted sesame seeds</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
